general.name: photoObj
general.description: The photoObj files contain the full, calibrated outputs of the SDSS imager photometric pipeline. They are parallel with the CAS photoObjAll and photoProfile tables. All "magnitudes" in this file are of the asinh type.
general.naming_convention: photoObj-[0-9]{6}-[1-6]-[0-9]{4}\.fits, where [0-9]{6} is a zero-padded six-digit number containing the run number, [1-6] is the camera column ('camcol') and [0-9]{4} is the zero-padded, four-digit frame sequence number.
